https://circuitjournal.com/50kg-load-cells-with-HX711#1x50
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LIuf2egMioA&t=598s

3D Printable Load Cell Mount:  https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2624188
HX711_ADC Arduino C++ library: https://github.com/olkal/HX711_ADC



Important note: "Measure the resistance of the load cell before connecting them.
The colors with the highest resistance connect to E+ and E- (excitation voltage).
It is NOT always red and black.
If the half bridge is done right, there should be less than 10mV between A+ and A- without weight."
